:::summary
Isaiah son of Amoz is the greatest prophet of the Old Testament — the "Shakespeare of the prophets" — whose book of 66 chapters encompasses the highest poetry, the deepest theology, and the most explicit messianic prophecy in all of Hebrew Scripture. Jesus quoted Isaiah more than any other Old Testament prophet, the New Testament cites Isaiah more than all other prophets combined, and the Savior himself commanded the Nephites in the Book of Mormon to "search these things diligently; for great are the words of Isaiah" (3 Nephi 23:1).
